HTML

Bat buoc phai co tag mo va tag dong cho mot doan ma html

<openingTag>content</closingTag>
<html>
	<body>
	</body>
</html>
	

elements:
1. <h1> </h1>
h1 -> h6: 
- used to signfy the importance of content, h2 elements have less importance than h1 elements

2. <p></p>: used to create a paragraph of text on websites

3. <!-- text -->: Commenting allows you to leave messages without affecting the browser display

4. identify different content areas (HTML5)
<main>
  <h1>Most important content of the document</h1>
  <p>Some more important content...</p>
</main> : used to represent the main content of the body of an HTML document
- Content inside the main element should be unique to the document and should not be repeated in other parts of the document.

5. nesting and indentation (lam to va thut dau dong): used to make HTML easier to read

6. <img>: add image to your website
- img elements have an opening tag without a closing tag. A tag for an element without a closing tag is known as a self-closing tag.
- src attributes: in an img element specifies the image's URL 
Ex: <img src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/cat-photo-app/relaxing-cat.jpg">












